There are now more than 100 people living inside the building which contravenes new regulations amid the coronavirus outbreak. CAPE TOWN - The refugee group living inside a church in the Cape Town CBD said they will not leave despite health concerns amid the coronavirus outbreak. Earlier this month, they were removed while others returned to seek refuge inside the Central Methodist Mission Church. There are now more than 100 people living inside the building which contravenes new regulations amid the coronavirus outbreak. #CTRefugees the group says they will continue to live on the street - in smaller groups due to hygiene concerns amid the coronavirus outbreak. JK pic.twitter.com/N6Oni71hiT  One of the refugee leaders, Aline Bukuru, said they will stay despite the issuing of the eviction order.